Description: Fragment of handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine red-brown, hard fired. Circular stamp.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Name Boethos. Perhaps from same die as Alexandria Museum, ALEX ABC 0918.34. Same die as 2011,5003.459.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0485)
